{"type":"text","timestamp":1773351738978,"sessionID":"ses_31c010c9effeOfeCSqmf0ROAdl","part":{"id":"prt_ce3ff944e002A4ZLCG6THuDLpR","sessionID":"ses_31c010c9effeOfeCSqmf0ROAdl","messageID":"msg_ce3ff872e001P6686YOCr3rT2R","type":"text","text":"## Goal\n\nImplement a \"dynamic agent-worker types\" feature for the wombo-combo (woco) AI agent orchestration system. This feature allows users to dynamically pull specialized agent definitions from the `msitarzewski/agency-agents` GitHub repository and use them instead of the default `wave-worker` agent when launching features. The work is on branch `feature/dynamic-agent-types` based on `main`.\n\n## Instructions\n\n- Follow the feature spec with 3 subtasks in order:\n  1. **Build agency-agents registry client** (`agent-registry-client`, 4h) — Fetch agent definitions from github.com/msitarzewski/agency-agents, parse their format, cache locally. Support listing available agents and fetching by name.\n  2. **Convert agency-agents format to woco agent template** (`agent-format-converter`, 4h) — Map agency-agents definition format to woco's wave-worker.md template format. Handle differences in structure, prompt style, and capabilities.\n  3. **Per-feature agent type selection** (`agent-selection-per-feature`, 2h) — Add an `agent` field to features YAML schema and `--agent` flag to launch. When launching, use the specified agent type instead of the default wave-worker.\n\n- **Constraints:**\n  - Must pull agent definitions from the agency-agents GitHub repo dynamically\n  - Must convert/adapt agency-agents format to woco's agent template format\n  - Must cache pulled agents locally to avoid repeated network calls\n  - Must support per-feature agent type selection (via features YAML or --agent flag)\n  - Must support offline mode with cached agents\n\n- **Forbidden:** Do not bundle all agents statically — they must be pulled from the registry\n\n- Use conventional commits scoped to `dynamic-agent-types`\n- Do NOT push to remote or modify `.features.yml`\n- Run `bun run build` to verify after completion\n\n## Discoveries\n\n### Agency-agents format\n- Each agent is a Markdown file with YAML frontmatter containing: `name`, `description`, `color`, `emoji`, `vibe`\n- The body is a full personality/instruction document with sections like: Identity & Memory, Core Mission, Critical Rules, Technical Deliverables (with code examples), Workflow Process, Communication Style, Success Metrics, Advanced Capabilities\n- Agents are organized in directories by division: `engineering/`, `design/`, `marketing/`, `testing/`, `support/`, `product/`, `project-management/`, `sales/`, `paid-media/`, `spatial-computing/`, `specialized/`, `game-development/` (with sub-dirs like `unity/`, `godot/`, `unreal-engine/`, `roblox-studio/`)\n- File naming convention: `{category}-{agent-name}.md` (e.g., `engineering-frontend-developer.md`)\n\n### Woco's wave-worker.md format\n- Also Markdown with YAML frontmatter, but uses `description` (long text) and `mode: primary`\n- The body contains operational rules specific to woco's autonomous agent behavior (worktree awareness, headless operation, commit guidelines, error recovery)\n- Located at `src/templates/wave-worker.md`, installed into `agent/wave-worker.md` in the project\n\n### GitHub API for fetching tree\n- Use `https://api.github.com/repos/msitarzewski/agency-agents/git/trees/main?recursive=1` to get full file listing\n- Raw content via `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/msitarzewski/agency-agents/main/{path}`\n- The tree has ~130+ agent .md files across all divisions\n\n### Key architecture understanding\n- `src/lib/templates.ts` — `ensureAgentDefinition()` checks/installs agent definition to `agent/{name}.md`\n- `src/lib/launcher.ts` — `launchHeadless()` passes `--agent config.agent.name` to the opencode binary\n- `src/commands/launch.ts` — Main launch flow: calls `ensureAgentDefinition()`, generates prompt, launches agents\n- `src/config.ts` — `WomboConfig.agent.name` defaults to `\"wave-worker\"`, `agent.configFiles` includes `\"agent/\"`\n- `src/lib/features.ts` — `Feature` interface has no `agent` field yet\n- `src/lib/prompt.ts` — `generatePrompt()` creates the feature prompt passed to the agent\n- `src/index.ts` — CLI arg parsing, no `--agent` flag yet\n\n## Accomplished\n\n- **Completed:** Full codebase exploration and understanding of all relevant files\n- **Completed:** Full understanding of the agency-agents repo format (fetched and analyzed frontmatter structure, directory layout, GitHub API tree endpoint)\n- **Completed:** Created a TodoWrite plan for all 3 subtasks\n- **Not started:** Actual code implementation (no files created or modified yet, no commits made)\n\n## Relevant files / directories\n\n### Files to CREATE:\n- `src/lib/agent-registry.ts` — Registry client (fetch, parse, cache, list, get by name)\n- `src/lib/agent-converter.ts` — Convert agency-agents format to woco agent template format\n\n### Files to MODIFY:\n- `src/lib/features.ts` — Add optional `agent` field to `Feature` interface\n- `src/lib/templates.ts` — Update `ensureAgentDefinition()` to support dynamic agent types\n- `src/lib/launcher.ts` — Pass dynamic agent name to the opencode binary\n- `src/commands/launch.ts` — Wire up `--agent` flag, resolve agent per feature\n- `src/index.ts` — Add `--agent` CLI flag parsing\n- `src/config.ts` — Possibly add registry config options (cache dir, repo URL)\n\n### Files READ (for context):\n- `src/templates/wave-worker.md` — Default agent template (80 lines)\n- `src/lib/prompt.ts` — Prompt generation (246 lines)\n- `src/lib/state.ts` — Wave/agent state management (247 lines)\n- `src/lib/monitor.ts`, `src/lib/verifier.ts`, `src/lib/merger.ts` — Referenced but not read\n- `package.json` — Dependencies: yaml, neo-blessed, mermaidtui\n- `tsconfig.json` — ES2022, ESNext modules, bundler resolution, strict mode, Bun types\n\n### External resources:\n- `https://api.github.com/repos/msitarzewski/agency-agents/git/trees/main?recursive=1` — Full file tree\n- `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/msitarzewski/agency-agents/main/{path}` — Raw file content\n- Example agents fetched: `engineering/engineering-frontend-developer.md`, `engineering/engineering-backend-architect.md`","time":{"start":1773351738977,"end":1773351738977}}}
